1. OVERVIEW
-----------
Track my app is a personal productivity tool for students to manage job
applications. Users can track each application's status, deadlines, pay, links, and
notes. The application provides smart alerts for approaching deadlines and stale
applications, as well as curated links to popular job boards.

---

2. ARCHITECTURE
---------------
The application is a monorepo with three workspaces:

  shared/   Shared TypeScript type definitions used by both api and web
  api/      Express.js REST API — handles all business logic and DB access
  web/      React SPA — user interface

Deployment topology:

  [Browser] --> [Cloudflare Pages] (React SPA)
                       |
                       | HTTPS (VITE_API_URL)
                       v
               [Railway] (Express API)
                       |
                       | Supabase JS client
                       v
               [Supabase] (PostgreSQL + Auth)

The frontend never connects directly to Supabase for data operations. All data flows
through the Express API, which uses the user's JWT to enforce row-level security.
The frontend uses Supabase only for authentication (sign in, sign up, session management).

---

3. TECHNOLOGY STACK
-------------------

Frontend
  - React 18 with TypeScript
  - Vite (build tool, dev server, module bundler)
  - Tailwind CSS v4 via @tailwindcss/vite plugin (no PostCSS config)
  - Custom theme colors defined in @theme block in index.css
  - TanStack Query (React Query) for server state and caching
  - Axios for HTTP requests
  - Radix UI for accessible components (Select, AlertDialog, Tooltip)
  - React Router v6 for client-side routing
  - Sonner for toast notifications

Backend
  - Node.js 20+
  - Express.js with TypeScript
  - Supabase JS client (server-side, uses user JWT for RLS)
  - Zod for request body validation
  - Helmet for HTTP security headers
  - CORS configured via ALLOWED_ORIGINS environment variable

Database
  - Supabase (hosted PostgreSQL)
  - Row-Level Security (RLS) on all user tables
  - Supabase Auth for user management and JWT issuance

Shared
  - TypeScript interfaces for Job, UserProfile, JobBoard, and enums
  - Zod schemas (CreateJobSchema, UpdateJobSchema) for validation

---

4. DATABASE DESIGN
------------------

4.1 Tables

  jobs
  ----
  id              UUID        Primary key (gen_random_uuid())
  user_id         UUID        FK → auth.users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE
  company         TEXT        Company name (required)
  title           TEXT        Position title (required)
  industry        TEXT        Industry category
  location        TEXT        Job location
  min_year        ENUM        Minimum year: freshman/sophomore/junior/senior/graduate/other
  job_link        TEXT        URL to the job posting
  app_link        TEXT        URL to the application portal
  status          ENUM        Job status (see 4.2)
  conference      TEXT        Career fair or conference name
  cover_letter    TEXT        URL to cover letter (must be http/https)
  pay             TEXT        Compensation (free text, e.g. "$25/hr")
  notes           TEXT        Free-form notes
  added           DATE        Date added (default: today)
  applied_date    DATE        Date application was submitted
  deadline        DATE        Application deadline
  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ Auto-set on insert
  updated_at      TIMESTAMPTZ Auto-updated via trigger

  user_profiles
  -------------
  user_id         UUID        PK + FK → auth.users(id)
  major           TEXT        User's academic major
  positions       TEXT[]      Preferred position types
  locations       TEXT[]      Preferred work locations

  job_boards
  ----------
  id              UUID        Primary key
  name            TEXT        Display name
  url             TEXT        Board URL
  category        TEXT        Grouping category
  description     TEXT        Short description
  sort_order      INTEGER     Display order within category

4.2 Job Status Enum

  not_started      Added but not yet worked on
  in_progress      Application in progress
  applied          Submitted
  offered          Offer received
  rejected         Rejected
  underqualified   Did not meet requirements
  missed_deadline  Deadline passed without applying
  archive          Manually archived
  other            Catch-all

4.3 Triggers

  jobs_updated_at       Auto-sets updated_at = NOW() on every UPDATE
  jobs_applied_date     Auto-sets applied_date = today when status changes TO 'applied'
                        and applied_date is not already set
  on_auth_user_created  Creates a user_profiles row when a new auth.users row is inserted

4.4 Row-Level Security

  All RLS policies use auth.uid() = user_id, ensuring users can only read and
  write their own data. job_boards has public read access (no user restriction).

4.5 Indexes

  idx_jobs_user_id      Speeds up all per-user queries
  idx_jobs_user_status  Speeds up filtered queries by status
  idx_jobs_deadline     Speeds up deadline-based sorting/filtering
  idx_jobs_added        Speeds up date-based sorting

---

5. BACKEND API
--------------

All routes (except /health) require a valid Supabase JWT in the Authorization header.
The API creates a per-request Supabase client using the user's JWT, so all DB queries
automatically respect RLS policies.

Base URL: https://internship-tracker-dev.up.railway.app

Endpoints:

  GET    /health                   Health check — returns { ok: true }

  GET    /api/jobs?year=2025       Fetch jobs for an academic year
                                   year param = start year of academic year
                                   Academic year: Aug 1 of year → Jul 31 of year+1
                                   Defaults to current academic year

  POST   /api/jobs                 Create a job (body validated by CreateJobSchema)
  PATCH  /api/jobs/:id             Update a job (body validated by UpdateJobSchema)
  DELETE /api/jobs/:id             Delete a job

  GET    /api/profile              Get the current user's profile
  PATCH  /api/profile              Update the current user's profile

  GET    /api/job-boards           Fetch all job boards ordered by sort_order

Input Sanitization:
  All text fields on job create/update pass through sanitizeJobInput(), which strips
  HTML tags using a regex replace (/<[^>]*>/g). This prevents stored XSS without
  requiring a DOM environment on the server.

---

6. FRONTEND APPLICATION
-----------------------

6.1 Routing

  /           DashboardPage   Main job tracking grid
  /job-boards JobBoardsPage   Curated job board links
  /profile    ProfilePage     User profile editor

  Protected routes redirect to /login when no authenticated session exists.

6.2 API Client

  web/src/api/client.ts exports an Axios instance with:
  - baseURL: import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL ?? '/api'
  - Request interceptor: attaches the current user's JWT as Bearer token

6.3 State Management

  Server state is managed by TanStack Query:
  - useJobs(year)         Fetches jobs for the given academic year (staleTime: 30s)
  - useJobBoards()        Fetches job boards (staleTime: 5 min)
  - useCreateJob()        POST mutation with cache invalidation
  - useUpdateJob()        PATCH mutation with cache invalidation
  - useDeleteJob()        DELETE mutation with cache invalidation
  - useMarkApplied()      PATCH shortcut to set status = 'applied'

  Authentication state is managed by AuthContext, which wraps the Supabase auth client
  and only sets the user when email_confirmed_at is present (preventing unconfirmed
  users from accessing the app).

---

7. AUTHENTICATION & SECURITY
-----------------------------

- Supabase Auth handles user registration, login, and JWT issuance
- Email confirmation is required before a user can log in
- JWTs are short-lived and automatically refreshed by the Supabase client
- The API validates JWTs on every request via the requireAuth middleware
- CORS is restricted to origins listed in ALLOWED_ORIGINS (comma-separated env var)
- HTTP security headers are set by Helmet
- Request bodies are validated by Zod schemas before processing
- All text inputs are HTML-stripped before DB insert/update
- The service role key is never exposed to the frontend

---

8. DASHBOARD & JOB GRID
------------------------

The dashboard is the primary screen. It shows a filterable, paginated list of jobs
for the selected academic year. On desktop, jobs display as a table. On mobile,
jobs display as stacked cards.

8.1 Quick Filters
-----------------
Filter pills displayed above the grid. Selecting one resets the page to 1.
All filtering is client-side on the currently fetched year's data.

  Active        Jobs with status: not_started, in_progress, interviewing
  Not Started   Jobs with status: not_started
  Applied       Jobs where applied_date is set
  Due Soon      Jobs where deadline is within DEADLINE_WINDOW days (5 days)
                and status is not applied or archive
  Stale         Jobs added more than MAX_STALE_DAYS ago (7 days) with no
                status progression (not applied, not archive)
  Conference    Jobs where conference field is set
  Archived      Jobs with status: archive
  All           No filter applied — shows all jobs for the selected year

  Each filter pill displays a count badge showing how many jobs match.

8.2 Academic Year Filter
------------------------
A dropdown selector to the right of the filter bar. Options show as "2025–2026"
style labels. The academic year runs August 1 of the start year through July 31
of the following year.

  Default: current academic year
    - If today is August or later: current calendar year is the start year
    - If today is before August: previous calendar year is the start year

  The year is sent to the API as a query param (?year=2025) and the API filters
  the jobs table by the added date falling within the academic year range.
  This reduces payload size by only returning relevant data.

8.3 Pagination
--------------
  PAGE_SIZE = 15 jobs per page (constant in DashboardPage)
  Pagination is client-side, applied after quick filtering.
  A pagination control bar is displayed above the grid showing:
  - Total job count and current page / total pages
  - Prev and Next buttons (disabled at boundaries)
  Pagination resets to page 1 when the quick filter or year changes.
  The control only appears when filtered results exceed PAGE_SIZE.

8.4 Grid Columns
----------------
The desktop table displays the following columns by default (left to right):

  Added         Date the job was added (formatted as Mon DD, YYYY)
  Status        Color-coded status badge
  Company       Multi-line cell (see 8.7 Inline Cell Layout)
  Location      Location with industry shown below in smaller text
  Applied       Date application was submitted
  Deadline      Application deadline (highlighted red when due soon)
  Links         Job posting link and apply link stacked vertically
  Cover         Link to cover letter document
  Notes         Truncated with full text shown on hover via tooltip
  Actions       Edit, Mark Applied, and Delete buttons (sticky right column)

8.5 Column Sorting
------------------
Clicking a column header sorts the grid by that column. Clicking again reverses
the sort direction. A ▲ or ▼ indicator appears next to the sorted column header.
Sortable columns: Added, Status, Company, Location, Applied, Deadline, Pay, Conf.
Non-sortable columns: Links, Cover, Notes, Actions.

8.6 Column Reordering
---------------------
Column headers (except Actions) can be dragged and dropped to reorder them.
The new order is persisted to localStorage under the key 'jobs-col-order'.
A version key ('jobs-col-order-v') is stored alongside the order. When
CURRENT_VERSION is bumped (on column schema changes), the saved order is cleared
and reset to the default to prevent stale column configurations.

8.7 Inline Cell Layout
-----------------------
To reduce column count, several fields are combined into single cells:

  Company cell (stacked vertically):
    Line 1: Company name + conference badge (if set)
             Conference badge styled as purple pill with "conf: <name>" prefix
    Line 2: Job title — Pay (pay shown only if set)
    Line 3: MinYear: <value> (shown only if min_year is set)

  Location cell (stacked vertically):
    Line 1: Location (or — if not set)
    Line 2: Industry in smaller gray text (shown only if set)

  Links cell (stacked vertically):
    Line 1: "Job" link (job_link)
    Line 2: "Apply" link (app_link, shown only if set)

---

9. ALERT SYSTEM
---------------
The AlertBar component appears below the header when there are actionable alerts.
It displays two types of pills:

  Due Soon pills (red)
    Shown for jobs where the deadline is within DEADLINE_WINDOW days (5).
    Excludes jobs with status applied or archive.
    Format: "Company — X days left" or "Company — due today"

  Stale pills (amber)
    Shown for jobs added more than MAX_STALE_DAYS ago (7) with no progression.
    Excludes jobs with status applied or archive.
    Company name is displayed in bold.

Constants defined in web/src/lib/dateUtils.ts:
  DEADLINE_WINDOW = 5   Days before deadline to trigger due-soon alert
  MAX_STALE_DAYS  = 7   Days since added to consider a job stale

---

10. JOB BOARDS PAGE
-------------------
A curated list of job application search sites stored in the job_boards database table.
Data is fetched via GET /api/job-boards and cached for 5 minutes.
Boards are grouped by category and displayed as cards with name, description, and
a link that opens in a new tab. Categories and boards are seeded via job-boards.sql
and are read-only (users cannot add or modify boards).

Categories (as seeded):
  General Job Boards
  Tech & Engineering
  Finance & Business
  Research & Academia

---

11. PROFILE PAGE
----------------
Users can set:
  - Major (free text)
  - Preferred positions (multi-value text input, stored as TEXT[])
  - Preferred locations (multi-value text input, stored as TEXT[])

Changes are saved via PATCH /api/profile. A profile row is auto-created when
the user first signs up via the on_auth_user_created trigger.

---

12. MOBILE EXPERIENCE
---------------------
A useMediaQuery hook detects screens narrower than 768px. On mobile:
  - The job table is replaced by a stacked card list (JobCardList component)
  - Navigation links are hidden from the header and moved into the UserMenu dropdown
  - The quick filter bar uses a Radix UI Select dropdown instead of pill buttons
  - The card list scrolls independently within a flex container

---

13. DEPLOYMENT
--------------
See docs/Deployment_Plan.md for full instructions.

  Backend (Railway)
    - Deployed from GitHub via Nixpacks
    - nixpacks.toml controls build: only builds shared and api workspaces
    - Node.js 20 specified in nixpacks.toml
    - Health check endpoint: GET /health
    - Environment variables set in Railway dashboard per environment
    - PORT is set automatically by Railway

  Frontend (Cloudflare Pages)
    - Deployed from GitHub, auto-deploys on push to configured branch
    - Build command: cd web && npm install && npm run build
    - Output directory: web/dist
    - Environment variables set in Cloudflare Pages dashboard
    - VITE_API_URL must include full URL with /api suffix

  Database (Supabase)
    - Schema applied manually via SQL Editor
    - RLS enforces data isolation between users
    - Email confirmation required (set in Authentication settings)
    - Site URL must be set to production frontend URL for confirmation emails
